Which runlevel is typically used for single user mode, as indicated in /etc/inittab?
A)  1
B)  2
C)  5
D)  6
A
A. Single- user mode is typically runlevel 1. In runlevel 1, no network services are started, andit is known as rescue.target in systemd. Runlevel 2 has networking but typically not ser-vices. Runlevel 5 is full multiuser with networking, and runlevel 6 is reboot.
